data.chText: 消耗，耗费（燃料、能量、时间等）
data.enText: to use sth, especially fuel, energy or time

data.chText: 电力工业消耗大量的矿物燃料。
data.enText: The electricity industry consumes large amounts of fossil fuels.

data.chText: 他死亡前喝了大量的酒。
data.enText: Before he died he had consumed a large quantity of alcohol.
to fill sb with a strong feeling

data.chText: 那座旅馆很快被大火吞噬。
data.enText: The hotel was quickly consumed by fire.

simple_means.memory_skill: con 加强 + sum 拿，取 + e → 拿完 → 消费

means: 消耗，耗费(燃料、能量、时间等)

example: The effort to pass the exam consumed all his energy

tr: serve oneself to, or consume regularly
example: Have another bowl of chicken soup!
I don't take sugar in my coffee
this car consumes a lot of gas
They run through 20 bottles of wine a week
Some people can down a pound of meat in the course of one meal

value.def: If you consume something, you eat or drink it.

example.ex: Many people experienced a drop in their cholesterol levels when they consumed oat bran.
example.tran: 很多人食用燕麦麸后胆固醇水平下降了。

example.ex: ...serving chocolate ice-creams for the children to consume in the kitchen.
example.tran: 端上巧克力冰激凌让孩子们在厨房里吃

value.def: To consume an amount of fuel, energy, or time means to use it up.

example.ex: Some of the most efficient refrigerators consume 70 percent less electricity than traditional models.
example.tran: 一些极为节能的冰箱比传统型号耗电减少70%。

example.ex: ...plans which will consume hours of time and deplete your cash reserves.
example.tran: 要花费若干小时并消耗你留存备用的钱的计划

value.tran: 消耗，耗费(燃料、能源或时间)

value.def: If a fire consumes a building, it completely destroys it.
If a feeling or idea consumes you, it affects you very strongly indeed.
value.tran: (使)沉溺，(使)沉迷，(使)充满(感情或思想)
